[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm looking into tracking dynamic access specifically for native images, not JVM tests. When building the native test executable with `-H:TrackDynamicAccess`, it seems to provide coverage outputs from the native compile/run. I'm considering how tests operate under Native Image without a SecurityManager, and I'm wondering if dynamic access can even be covered during that process. I realize the `SecurityManager` class exists but can't be set, and I might also be able to catch exceptions during testing, though that wouldn't help with coverage.
